According to the Intel TDX Documentation the TME-MT memory integrity can be either enable or disabled both works for TDX.
On the latest BIOS versions of some manufacturer the settings to specifically set the TME-MT Memory Integrity is not available.

the `TME MSR 0x982: 0x100168000000b` is not to check if the TME-MT Memory Integrity is disabled or enabled but to check theses parameters:
```The IA32_TME_ACTIVATE register uses the following bit fields (from least significant to most significant, bits 0 to 63)  ￼ ￼:
    •    Bit 0 (Lock): indicates if the MSR is locked.
    •    Bit 1 (TmeEnable): enables hardware memory encryption (TME) and is required to enable MKTME.
    •    Bit 2 (KeySelect): 0 = generate new key; 1 = restore from standby.
    •    Bit 3 (SaveKeyForStandby): save key for standby resume.
    •    Bits 7:4 (TmePolicy): selects encryption algorithm (e.g., AES-XTS-128, AES-XTS-128 with integrity, AES-XTS-256).
    •    Bits 35:32 (MkTmeKeyidBits): number of KeyID bits for MKTME (must be non-zero and TmeEnable must be set to use MKTME).
    •    Bits 63:48 (MkTmeCryptoAlgs): bitmask indicating which MKTME encryption algorithms are allowed by BIOS.```
